; Notes:
;   A wagon that can travel thru normal rooms or through a land
;   with dozens of simulated rooms (100 rooms in this version).
;   Station Alpha is the station near Fayd where people board the wagon.
;   Type RECALL for gm help.
;   Item 0 at any room the wagon travels to must be reserved for the wagon.
; To Do:
;   Have multiple wagons in a caravan
;   Have other wagons in other parts of the map
;   Allow someone to mount the wagon or an animal as the pilot
;   Allow travel thru normal rooms
;   Set up automatic travel
;   Allow a player to act as the driver with n,s,e,w verbs.
; Bugs:
;   Using a single room for any arbitrary stop means that unless the
;   players are prevented from dropping things, it will look odd to find
;   the same dropped items at a 'different' stop. Perhaps Stop! should
;   be reserved for gm's.
; Sequence:
;   If someone enters and variables aren't initialized, initialize them
;   Set some variables for this pass
;   If something is put in the window, delete it and reduce the load, if any
;   Process spoken commands
;   If direction given
;     Ignore if already in motion
;     Report if wagon still stuck in rut, or fallen into rut
;     Test limits of travel
;     Have driver acknowledge the direction, or tell of error
;   If we're going to move
;     If we're leaving a station
;       Remove wagon from station and echo that it's left
;       Remove the exit from the wagon
;     If new room has obstacle, prevent motion
;     Echo that the wagon is moving
;     Set flag to ignore motion commands
;     Put player in round time
;     After delay clear flag so driver listens again
;     Adjust current 'location' based on directions
;   If we're showing a scene (from looking or moving)
;     If we've arrived at a station
;       Add the wagon to the station
;       Change the wagon's exit to the station room
;       Unlock the door
;     Set the terrain based on longitude and use as 1st description fragment
;     Set the vegetation based on latitude and use as 2nd description fragment
;     Select a 3rd description fragment from current location somewhat randomly
;     Show the room to the player (if they looked) or everyone (if we moved)
; Variables:
;  DUMMY1 holds random numbers and other temporaries
;  DUMMY2 hold the current command
;  DUMMY3 holds the number of the third phrase.
;  DUMMY4 is the X direction
;  DUMMY5 is the Y direction